# Cookbook Memory — example environment variables
#
# Copy this file to `.env` (gitignored) and fill values as needed.
# Every var below has a documented source-of-truth ADR; see docs/adrs/.
#
# Loading: every entrypoint that reads these vars calls
# `memeval.dotenv_loader.load_root_dotenv()` at startup — daydream-cli, the
# bench runner, the pipeline orchestrator, the plugin CLI, and the Stop-hook
# handler. Existing env vars WIN over `.env` (override=False). So either edit
# `.env` here OR `export` in your shell (export wins). To force a specific
# `.env`, set `MEMEVAL_DOTENV=/path/to/.env`.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Daydreaming — required for `daydream-cli daydream` + `daydream-cli dream`
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Absolute path to the memory-store DIRECTORY. Resolved by ADR-dreaming-019's
# `resolve_basedir()` — the engine writes per-session state under
# `$MEMORY_STORE/dream/` and MarkdownStore docs under `$MEMORY_STORE/markdown/`.
# Unset → KeyError; missing path → auto-mkdir'd; points at a file → ValueError.
# Both error modes fail-open at the daydream-cli boundary (ADR-018) but the
# engine cannot proceed. Plugin convention: `${CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR}/.cookbook-memory`.
MEMORY_STORE=/absolute/path/to/memory-store

# OpenRouter API key for the subconscious model (ADR-dreaming-012). Unset →
# the engine emits `llm_unavailable` + `chunk_skipped_unavailable_llm` events
# and the cursor does NOT advance (ADR-dreaming-013), so the next Stop pass
# catches up once the key is set.
OPENROUTER_API_KEY=

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Daydreaming — optional overrides
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Subconscious-LLM provider + model. Defaults: `openrouter` +
# `inclusionai/ling-2.6-flash` (ADR-dreaming-004). Swap to test alternative
# free-tier OpenRouter models or future provider implementations.
# Active test target (ADR-dreaming-022): DREAM_MODEL=deepseek/deepseek-v4-flash
# DREAM_PROVIDER=openrouter
# DREAM_MODEL=inclusionai/ling-2.6-flash

# EXTRACTION_SYSTEM_PROMPT variant selector (ADR-dreaming-023). Default = V0
# when unset, preserving the original MODERATE-threshold prompt. Uncomment
# exactly one of the lines below to opt into a variant. Variant names are
# case-insensitive; unknown values raise ValueError at the first daydream call.
#
#   V0 = current baseline. MODERATE selectivity, chat-shaped INCLUDE/REJECT
#        examples. Backward-compatible default — no opt-in needed.
#   V1 = STRICT (annoyance-prevention only). Drops named decisions, drops
#        decisions-with-rationale, drops implicit commitments. Keeps only
#        explicit user-named identity / preferences / rule-form constraints /
#        explicitly-asked commitments. WARNING: bench data shows V1 extracts
#        zero memories from autonomous-agent transcripts (no "remember this"
#        markers from a non-interactive agent). Use only if a human is in-loop
#        with the agent frequently issuing explicit save-this directives.
#   V2 = A-MEM (keywords + context fields per memory). Adds FAISS-friendly
#        keyword array + future-relevance context sentence to each memory.
#        WARNING: the recall path does NOT yet read these fields — they reach
#        the LLM output but `_build_memory_item` drops them. Wiring to the
#        recall surface is a follow-up; until then V2 is observable but the
#        retrieval benefit is unrealized.
#   V3 = SWE-tuned (in-domain code examples). Opener reframed for an
#        autonomous coding agent. INCLUDE block uses engineering preferences,
#        project conventions, named decisions with rationale, ongoing commits.
#        REJECT block extended with code-shaped anchors (pytest output, diff
#        lines, transient implementation narration). Top performer on bench-
#        data sweep 2026-06-23; recommended for SWE-CL-shaped workloads.
# DREAM_EXTRACTION_VARIANT=V0
# DREAM_EXTRACTION_VARIANT=V1
# DREAM_EXTRACTION_VARIANT=V2
# DREAM_EXTRACTION_VARIANT=V3

# Per-session-state retention TTL in days. Default: 30 (ADR-dreaming-015).
# Files under `dream/` older than this are swept on the next invocation.
# DREAM_RETENTION_DAYS=30

# Sweeper-throttle in minutes between scans. Default: 60 (ADR-dreaming-015).
# DREAM_SWEEP_INTERVAL_MIN=60

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Voyage AI — embeddings + reranker (optional, ADR-storage-003)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Voyage API key for `VoyageEmbedder` (`stores/embedders.py`) + `VoyageReranker`
# (`stores/rerankers.py`). Auto-selects the `accuracy` recall profile in
# `build_store()` when set; absent → router falls back to the `fusion` profile
# (`dreaming/cli.py:96-97`). Get a key at https://dash.voyageai.com.
# VOYAGE_API_KEY=

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Router — retrieval profile + local embeddings / ANN (optional)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# The store stack that `build_store()` assembles (vectors + markdown + graph behind a
# RouterStore) auto-selects a RECALL PROFILE. Precedence (plugin/cookbook_memory/core/contract.py):
#   1. $MEMORY_PROFILE if set: speed | fusion | fusion-local | fusion-falkor | accuracy |
#      accuracy-local (explicit always wins)
#   2. else $MEMEVAL_LOCAL_ANN=1  -> accuracy-local  (local MiniLM + sqlite-vec ANN, no API key)
#   3. else $VOYAGE_API_KEY set   -> accuracy        (Voyage embedder; see the section above)
#   4. else                       -> fusion          (offline RRF — best dependency-free recall)
# `speed` (the bare rule router) is never auto-selected; reach it only via $MEMORY_PROFILE=speed.
# `fusion-falkor` is never auto-selected either; reach it only via $MEMORY_PROFILE=fusion-falkor
# (see $FALKORDB_URL below).
# MEMORY_PROFILE=

# Recall score FLOOR — precision over the FINAL recall hits. Recall is top-k with no floor, so it can
# return k weak matches even when none is a real hit; this drops every hit scoring below the floor, so a
# weak/all-garbage recall returns fewer than k hits (or none) instead. When SET it overrides for ANY
# profile; a value <= 0 (e.g. RECALL_MIN_SCORE=0) DISABLES the floor. When UNSET, only the `accuracy`
# profile gets a default of 0.15 — the accuracy-calibrated value from n=52 real accuracy/Voyage recalls
# (PROVISIONAL: garbage recalls topped <= 0.09, real matches >= 0.189, so 0.15 sits in the gap). Every
# other profile defaults to NO floor (only accuracy was measured). Set a float to override.
# RECALL_MIN_SCORE=0.15

# External FalkorDB connection target for the opt-in `fusion-falkor` profile. ONLY read when
# $MEMORY_PROFILE=fusion-falkor — that profile is the `fusion` config with its graph backend swapped
# for an external FalkorDB the plugin CONNECTS to (`native=True`); every other backend is identical
# to `fusion`. Default: redis://localhost:6379. A Docker FalkorDB must be running and reachable at
# this URL (e.g. `docker run -p 6379:6379 falkordb/falkordb`) — `fusion-falkor` FAILS LOUD if it is
# not, and does NOT fall back to the in-memory graph (a silent fallback would mislabel the graph
# backend and corrupt a fusion-vs-fusion-falkor measurement).
# FALKORDB_URL=redis://localhost:6379

# Opt into LOCAL semantic retrieval — MiniLM (all-MiniLM-L6-v2, 384d) embeddings + sqlite-vec
# ANN, no API key. Requires the optional extra:
#     uv pip install -e 'eval[local-ann]'      # installs sentence-transformers + sqlite-vec
# With the extra (or model) absent it falls back to the offline fusion profile, so this is safe
# to leave set. Set to 1 to select the `accuracy-local` profile (see precedence above).
# MEMEVAL_LOCAL_ANN=1

# The MiniLM embedder loads its model with local_files_only by default (no surprise network
# fetch). On a machine that has never cached the model, set this to 1 to allow a ONE-TIME
# download from Hugging Face; otherwise pre-cache the model. Without a cached model AND without
# this flag, the vector backend falls back to the deterministic hashing embedder (no real
# semantics) — useful to know if local-ANN results look no better than lexical.
# MEMEVAL_ALLOW_MODEL_DOWNLOAD=1

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Cursor CLI harness (optional — for `--harness cursor`, ADR-harness-013/014)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# API key for the Cursor CLI (`cursor-agent`) when running the pipeline/bench with
# the `--harness cursor` run option (e.g.
# `make pipeline ARGS="--yes --harness cursor …"` or `memeval-bench --harness cursor`).
# REQUIRED for that harness and nothing else — the default Claude harness ignores it.
#
# Why a key (not the Cursor login): on macOS Cursor's interactive login is
# keychain-bound (no copyable token file), exactly like Claude Code. The API key is
# the ONLY keychain-free, headless auth path (the binary's auth priority is
# auth-token -> api-key -> login), which is what lets each pipeline STAGE run in its
# own isolated `HOME` sandbox — and in parallel — without an interactive /login
# (ADR-harness-014). Generate one at https://cursor.com/dashboard.
#
# Isolation note: the Cursor harness sandboxes config via a fresh `HOME` per run
# (relocating ~/.cursor/{mcp.json,cli-config.json,auth}); `CURSOR_DATA_DIR` only
# moves transcripts and does NOT isolate config — so the harness sets `HOME`, not
# `CURSOR_DATA_DIR`, for config isolation. Your host ~/.cursor is never touched.
# CURSOR_API_KEY=
#
# Alternatively a CURSOR_AUTH_TOKEN (higher-priority `auth-token` source) is also
# accepted by the harness; set only one.
# CURSOR_AUTH_TOKEN=
#
# Optional: override the cursor-agent binary path (else discovered on PATH /
# ~/.local/bin/cursor-agent).
# CURSOR_AGENT_CLI=/custom/path/to/cursor-agent

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Per-task checkout — local repo mirror cache (optional)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Directory holding persistent BARE git mirrors that EVERY per-task github checkout
# in a run draws on instead of fetching fresh from github.com — both graders
# (SwebenchHostGrader, LocalExecGrader) AND the agent-side checkouts that clone the
# repo the agent works in (the Claude and Cursor CLI code agents). Unset → unchanged:
# each checkout does a live shallow `git fetch` (a transient github timeout then drops
# that task — for an agent-side checkout that fails the WHOLE task, not just grading).
# Set → each repo is mirrored ONCE (`git clone --mirror`, the only network cost —
# minutes per repo, then reused), and every per-task checkout is a network-free local
# clone. A stale/missing mirror best-effort updates then falls back to the network
# path, so the cache never turns a workable checkout into a failure. Recommended for
# long multi-hour runs.
# MEMEVAL_REPO_CACHE=/absolute/path/to/repo-mirror-cache

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Anthropic real-model runs (optional, for the `[anthropic]` extra)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Required only when an AnthropicAdapter or AnthropicClient is in use.
# Stripped from every `claude` CLI invocation by the bench runner so it never
# leaks into subscription-authed calls.
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Langfuse observability (optional — ADR-harness-007)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Set all three to ship dream events to a Langfuse instance. Unset → events
# stay in the per-session JSONL diary only (ADR-dreaming-009).
# LANGFUSE_HOST=https://cloud.langfuse.com
# LANGFUSE_PUBLIC_KEY=
# LANGFUSE_SECRET_KEY=
